title: Barry Manilow - The Greatest Hits and Then Some... [1993] DVD5
description: Barry Manilow - The greatest hits and then some... [1993] DVD5 Barry Manilow (born Barry Alan Pincus; June 17, 1943) is an American singer-songwriter, arranger, musician and producer with a career that has spanned more than 50 years. His hit recordings include "Mandy", "Can't Smile Without You", and "Copacabana (At the Copa) The king of soft rock, Barry Manilow is one of America's most popular vocalists, especially among the older set. This video features Barry performing twelve of his best loved hits in their entirety, plus four remarkable medleys. Filmed live at London's Wembley Arena in April, 1993, the selections performed include: "The Best of Me," "Ready To Take a Chance Again," "Daybreak," "Copacabana," "I Write the Songs" and more.
